            java.lang.String spacecraft,
            java.util.Date aos,

Create a pass object.

Parameters:
station - The location where the pass was observed. This name should match an entry in the database's Stations table, but it is not required.
spacecraft - The spacecraft name. The name will be converted to all uppercase.
aos - Acquisition of signal
los - Loss of signal

setDeleteProtection

public void setDeleteProtection(boolean deleteProtected)
Set the delete protection field. This field is only effective is it is set prior to storing the pass in the database. If true, the DSM agents will not routinely delete this pass from the database.

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
Two passes are equal if they have the same database ID. If two passes have same spacecraft, AOS, and LOS but different IDs, this method will return false.
